  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 5 min, then fill a bowl of<strong> very cold water</strong> and add the <strong>cooked egg[s]</strong> to the bowl to cool down quickly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1721295968569-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1721295968569-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1721295968569-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1721295968569-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1721295968569-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut you <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>baking paper</strong> to avoid mess!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch<strong> </strong>of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set the tray aside until later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1721296057005-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1721296057005-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1721296057005-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1721296057005-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1721296057005-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a sheet of <strong>baking paper</strong> to your chopping board and sprinkle over a generous dusting of <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Remove your <strong>sausages </strong>from their skins and combine to form 1 giant meatball per person, then flatten the meatball[s] into a circle (big enough to coat an egg) onto the floured baking paper</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1721296060295-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1721296060295-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1721296060295-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1721296060295-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1721296060295-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the baking tray with the chips in the oven for 30 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>Peel the <strong>cooled egg[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>peeled egg[s]</strong> to the centre of your <strong>sausage meat circle[s]</strong></p><p>Wrap the sausage meat around the egg and seal it tightly on all sides so that there aren't any gaps – this is your <strong>sausage-coated egg</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1721296067200-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
